        {
            "block_label": "figure_title",
            "block_content": "represent the wild-type (LuxSit) amino acids. The rank of wild-type ddG_bind for each position screened for activity is shown with a heat map in c. d–f, The wild-type ddG_bind of the residues designed for d,e, π–π stacking or f, hydrophobic interactions were the lowest compared to the mutation ddG_bind values. This shows that the sequence is near-optimal for substrate binding and the design model is reliable.",
